= Motion Vector =
#context: vop
#type: node

"""Outputs a screen-space motion vector scaled to pixel dimensions."""

== Overview ==

Motion Vector converts the standard camera-space velocity vector into a screen-space motion vector scaled to pixel units. Use the output as a motion vector AOV for compositing motion blur or optical flow effects.

@parameters

Width Pixel (Multiply):
    #id: width_pixel
    Horizontal resolution used to scale the X component of the motion vector. Default is `1920`.

Height Pixel (Multiply):
    #id: height_pixel
    Vertical resolution used to scale the Y component of the motion vector. Default is `1080`.

@outputs

Motion Vector:
    Screen-space motion vector in pixel units.
